Rating: 0
Slow cooker modification: Brown ribs. Place in slow cooker. Coat with salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, coriander - plus 1/2 tsp chipotle pepper, 1 T smoked paprika and 7 ounces of chicken broth. Cook on low for 6 hours. Refrigerate. Skim fat. Reheat (tented in foil) in 350 oven for 40 minutes. Remove meat from bone and soak in pan juices. Fill ramekins 1/2 way with noodles or rice and top with savory meat and any remaining pan juices.

