Rating: 0
I've lived in Mexico, been a successful Mexican chef, taught Mexican cuisine, been a Mexican food consultant for over 50 years. I would never use 'chili powder' or ahahein peppers together in a dish with chilpotle, nor olive oil-use vegetable oil,nor black pepper. When you are using chile chilpotle you have the proper flavour. You should never put two chiles together that don't marry well. Chili Powder should not be used especially when you are using such a wonderful chile-which means in Nahua-"smoked chile." And why on earth would you need black pepper? That's a European idea. Be careful of the amount of chilpotle- 1 1/2 tablespoons is a bit excessive in relation to the amount of tomatoes. And the tomatoes should be pureed. What's the lime juice for?

