I thought this was great, and with short ribs, slow and low is the way to go. Let it go for hours, if you want (who cares if the meat falls off the bone before it makes it to the plate) - that's what braising is all about. As far as the Pot Roast comments, I'm sure it's good, too, but a pot roast and short ribs are hardly interchangeable.

Rating: 4
We used boneless short ribs from Costco. Don't worry about over cooking, we cooked an additional hour. Remove as much fat as you can, it will be quite reduced after skimming off the fat but the flavors mellow, then add 1/4 cup cream (this is not a low cal recipe). Buy good quality corn torillas and wrap the meat (semi-shredded), top with cilantro, lime and maybe a little sour cream. Black beans as a side and a salad. Yum

