Rating: 4
We loved this recipe with its savory, spicy flavor. I could not find canned chipotle chilis, so I substituted a liquid chipotle puree and it tasted great. To reduce the fat almost entirely, you can chill this for a few hours or overnight, and the fat rises to the top and solidifies so that it is easy to remove. We ate 1/2 of this dish the first night, and on the 2nd night, I tried taking the meat off of the bones, and added 1 can of corn kernels and 1 can of black beans to the mix and sprinkled chopped cilantro over the top. It was more like a stew and was very tasty.

